<TITLE> Ruling party using parliament to smear opposition: BNP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 30 (bdnews24.com)The ruling party has transformed parliament into a place to smear the reputation of the opposition party, the BNP secretary general said on Friday. The government is inventing stories against Ziaur Rahman, Khaleda Zia and their family and running a smear campaign against the opposition, Khandaker Delwar Hossain said, reacting to the remarks of Awami League MP Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim. On Thursday, Selim alleged in the parliament that Khaleda was involved in the Aug 21, 2004 grenade attack and the "conspiracy" which led to last week's bomb attack on ruling party MP Sheikh Fazle Noor Taposh. "The false, fabricated remarks of the ruling party MP proves that the government is involved in a deep conspiracy to destroy BNP," said Delwar at his Armanitola residence. He said the stories were being told to divert the focus of people from the failure of the government. Blaming the government directly for an ineffective parliament, he said, "Today it has become clear to the people why BNP is not going to parliament." "They never believed in democracy. They snatched the freedom of speech through BAKSAL (one-party rule in 1975). "When (military chief) H M Ershad took power forcefully and imposed military rule then Sheikh Hasina said, 'I am not unhappy'. That means they supported autocracy whether that was by BAKSAL or by supporting military rulers." He urged the government to leave the way of repression and offered assistance. b
